genresAdvancedInfo.name: tibetan traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Tibetan traditional music is a genre that has been passed down through generations of Tibetan musicians. It is characterized by its use of traditional instruments such as the dranyen, dramyin, and piwang, and its focus on storytelling and religious themes. Tibetan traditional music is often performed at festivals, weddings, and other cultural events, and is an important part of Tibetan identity and heritage.
